description.plain:
The self-proclaimed King of the Anthems, DJ Khaled is an American record producer, DJ, radio personality, record label executive, actor, author and social media aficionado.

Born in New Orleans—but based out of Miami—Khaled got his early start in the music business working as circuit DJ, hosting shows on the Miami-based radio station WEDR, and as the official DJ for the Terror Squad.

After years of cultivating relationships with high-profile artists, in 2006 Khaled released his star-studded debut album Listennn… the Album. He has since gone on to release nine studio albums, with his tenth project, Grateful, released in June 23th 2017.

In 2008 Khaled launched his record label We the Best Music Group, which currently operates as an imprint of Epic Records after previously being linked to Def Jam South and Cash Money Records. In 2009, Khaled was announced as the President of Def Jam South; his tenure ended in 2012.

As popular as his anthems are, Khaled’s ability to craft catchphrases and deliver “Major Keys” to the social media masses has launched him to super-stardom. These “Keys” include asking for blessings from his lion statuette, using cocoa butter, and having a weekly massage. His Snapchat stories are well-known, and average 2 million views per snap.

Khaled is currently signed to Epic Records and managed by Jay Z and his Roc Nation Management company.

description.plain:
“I’m the One” features a star-studded line-up of artists in especially braggadocio spirits, with Justin Bieber, Chance The Rapper, Lil Wayne and Quavo boasting to the women in their lives that they are “the only one” for them. “I’m the One” is Khaled’s second single from his 2017 album Grateful, following the February release of “Shining.”

The collaboration was teased throughout videos and pictures via the Instagram profiles of the featured artists, showing the making of the music video.

The song debuted at No.1 on the Billboard Hot 100 chart and UK Official Singles Chart. It became the second song to debut at #1 on the Hot 100 in 2017 making it Bieber’s second feat and Khaled’s first.

description.plain:
DJ Khaled links up R&B singers Rihanna & Bryson Tiller  for the fourth single released on 16th of June, 2017, off his studio album, Grateful.

Sampling Santana’s classic 1999 track, “Maria Maria,” the song finds Rihanna and Bryson singing to their lover on how they bring out “wild thoughts” when they’re together.

The song debuted on number 4 of the Billboard Hot 100 chart, and reached the Top 10 in other countries of Europe.

description.plain:
“For Free” is DJ Khaled and Drake’s summer ode to good sex. In it, Drake references Kendrick Lamar’s 2015 song “For Free?” and intentionally keeps the hook ambiguous, playing with the idea of men and women paying for sex.

Earlier, on Khaled’s Snapchat, he talked about “the Drake vocals finally [being] in,” referencing the then unreleased song.

The song samples lyrics and cadences from Too $hort’s “Blow The Whistle” and interpolates Akinyele’s “Fuck Me For Free.” The funky guitar riff underpinning the beat is sampled from 17:30 in [|] by Majid Jordan.

“For Free” is the fourth collaboration between DJ Khaled and Drake, following “No New Friends,” “I’m On One,” and “Fed Up.” Khaled also put an ad-lib at the end of Drake’s “Summer Sixteen.”

The track was just certified gold by the RIAA, meaning it’s sold over 500,000 copies.

description.plain:
On this balladic anthem — “one for the ladies” — DJ Khaled recruits an impressive line-up of R&B crooners and rappers for a sexy, sweet, piano-driven tune that samples Lil Jon’s crunk slow jam “Lovers and Friends.”

“Do You Mind" is the fourth single and one of the most star-studded cuts off DJ Khaled’s ninth studio album, Major Key. The song features all of the same artists who contributed to Khaled’s 2014 single “Hold You Down”, which is also his seventh top 40 hit. The song premiered on July 28, 2016 on iHeart Radio, and was later released on iTunes and Apple Music.

Nicki Minaj has appeared on three of the last four Khaled albums — she missed 2015’s I Changed A Lot and now’s back on Major Key. Rick Ross is the only rapper that’s been featured on every single DJ Khaled album since the first one in 2006, even multiple times on each record. In fact, his verse on “Do You Mind” is his twenty–ninth feature for a Khaled studio project, and definitely not the last one.

description.plain:
“GREECE” is one of the dual lead singles—along with “POPSTAR”—from DJ Khaled’s twelfth studio album, KHALED KHALED. Both tracks feature Drake and are Khaled’s first releases since his May 2019 album, Father of Asahd.

On the song, Drake promises his significant other a luxurious lifestyle, including vacations to Greece and expensive clothing. He then switches up the mood at the end of the song, where he discusses relationship problems that stem from his wealth and status.

The song was first previewed during an Instagram Live session Drake had on May 1, 2020, the day his fifth commercial mixtape, Dark Lane Demo Tapes, was released. Two months later, on June 30, 2020, Khaled and Drake both posted pictures of owls—the symbol of Drake’s OVO Sound imprint—teasing a possible collaboration between them. On July 15, 2020, Khaled posted the song’s release date and cover art on his Instagram account.

description.plain:
“I Got The Keys” is an anthem for success. The song channels DJ Khaled’s inspirational “major key” Snapchat mantra and is the second single from the his ninth studio album, also titled Major Key. Jay Z references winning the “Big Pimpin'” lawsuit, being the first of his kind in the rap game, and owning his recording masters — delivering subliminal jabs at any artist who isn’t “free” like him. As of July 29, 2016 the track has peaked at #30 on the Billboard Hot 100.

In an interview with Rap Radar Khaled explained that he traveled to Jay’s house in Los Angeles to play him the instrumental in his in-home studio.

I play him the record and I’m vibing, you know, I got that eye so I’m looking to the side, I don’t want him to know I’m looking, and I see him vibing. The first part is an instrumental so that’s when I’m really looking because, the great ones, that’s when they really just start going so I look and I just see him start rhyming in his head and mumbling… When the beat stopped, he’s just like, “Leave that for me.”

The next day Khaled was called back to the house to hear Hov’s contribution. The video announcing the partnership between Khaled and Roc Nation contains the footage of the first time Hov ever spat this first verse for Khaled.



During his We The Best Radio show Khaled announced that the video would premier after 2016’s BET Awards:

This video is powerful. It’s iconic. It’s amazing. First of all, Jay Z don’t shoot no videos. He barely shoots his own videos. It’s very rare that you see the icon Jay Z. Very rare.

https://twitter.com/djkhaled/status/747543287989297152

Jay Z is known to not shoot many music videos, especially not for his features. But Khaled knew this was going to be an epic track, so he kept proposing to Hov that they shoot a video:

All our fans expect us … to go all out! I don’t want to drop this song without a video. Anybody else who got a Jay-Z song with Future would drop it right away. I held it … because if I had dropped it I wouldn’t have got the video. I told Jigga I want people to see and feel it. You the Don, so let’s give them a visual!
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SFLSOIufuhM

songs.full_title: POPSTAR by DJ Khaled (Ft. Drake)
songs.title: POPSTAR

description.plain:
“POPSTAR” is one of the dual lead singles—along with “GREECE”—from DJ Khaled’s twelfth studio album, KHALED KHALED. Both tracks feature Drake and are Khaled’s first releases since his May 2019 album, Father of Asahd.

On the song, Drake likens himself to a pop star and the lifestyle that comes with being one—girls calling him nonstop, sporting credit cards with high spending limits, and buying large numbers of expensive watches. He also name-drops pop singers Ariana Grande, Selena Gomez and Justin Bieber, adding to the “pop star” theme of the song.

On June 30, 2020, Khaled and Drake both posted pictures of owls—the symbol of Drake’s OVO Sound imprint—teasing a possible collaboration between them. On July 15, 2020—two days before the song’s official release—Khaled posted the song’s release date and cover art on his Instagram account.

On September 4, 2020, the song’s official music video was released. Justin Bieber, who’s mentioned in the song, makes a cameo in the video and acts as a stand-in for Drake.

https://www.twitter.com/djkhaled/status/830999390516961281?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw

The single art features Khaled’s newborn son, Asahd Tuck Khaled.

The song samples “Dionne” by Osunlade, who sampled “Walk the way You Talk” by Dionne Warwick. DJ Khaled uses the instrumentals as well as the vocals from “Dionne” while adding his own fresh perspective.

songs.title: Top Off

description.plain:
On “Top Off,” Future, JAY-Z, and Beyoncé flex their wealth and luxurious lifestyles, epitomized by a chorus referencing the exclusive Maybach Landaulet. Both Bey and Jay also call for Philadelphia rapper and Roc Nation artist Meek Mill to be freed from prison, which follows on from Jay’s November 2017 New York Times op-ed on Meek and the trap of probation.

“Top Off” is the first single from DJ Khaled’s eleventh studio album, Father of Asahd. This is the first time Future, JAY-Z, and Bey have appeared on the same song. The song was first teased by Khaled via an Instagram post on March 1, 2018 that featured a video of him and his son Asahd vibing to the song in their Maybach Landaulet, with the song’s title being revealed at the end.

The track became JAY-Z and Beyoncé’s first Top 40 hit since 2014’s “Drunk In Love.”

description.plain:
On “Holy Key,” Kendrick Lamar and Big Sean trade verses that focus on religion, politics, discrimination and police brutality, while soul legend Betty Wright handles the church-like chorus.

The song is the third single off DJ Khaled’s Major Key,  following the Drake-assisted “For Free,” and Jay Z and Future collab “I Got The Keys”.

In the days leading up to the release of “Holy Key,” DJ Khaled teased that Kendrick would have the most talked about verse on his album:

https://twitter.com/Genius/status/755506266995294208

Khaled spoke about the collaboration process at a NYC listening party in July 2016:

I told Kendrick that I needed him to catch the Holy Ghost. No rules, no nothing. I told Big Sean the same thing. After I got the verses I got Ms. Wright, and I gave her some vibes, the tools for this hook. Basically, I told her to go to church.

description.plain:
“All I Do Is Win” is a standout track on DJ Khaled’s Victory. It features the autotune prowess of T-Pain on the chorus, the impressive flow of Ludacris, the rawness of Rick Ross and the swaggerific aloofness of Snoop Dogg.

The uplifting and motivational vibes given off, this proclaims it a track worthy of banging whilst going H.A.M. on the treadmill.

Notable Appearances in Pop Culture :


Several sports teams have used this as their theme song for home victories. It was most notably used by the Auburn Tigers football team during their 2010 national championship season. They played it during their pregame entrance and after every home game victory; they literally did not lose a game that year.
President Obama stepped up to the podium with this track for his speech at the 2013 White House Correspondents' Association Dinner.
Emma Stone blew the roof off in her “Lip Sync Battle” against Jimmy Fallon.

description.plain:
On “SORRY NOT SORRY,” DJ Khaled recruits rap titans Nas and Jay-Z, as well as vocalists James Fauntleroy and Beyoncé (under the alias Harmonies by The Hive.) He explained how the song came together with Ebro for Apple Music.

The track sees DJ Khaled sampling Jay-Z’s May 2002 hit, “Song Cry” for a smooth beat with heavy drums, accompanied by vocals from Beyoncé and Fauntleroy.

The song was first seen in an April 29th Instagram post, a day before the release. The post included a picture of the tracklist with the song being listed as the ninth song, but being moved to the tenth song in the updated track list.

“EVERY CHANCE I GET” is the 2nd track on DJ Khaled’s 12th studio album KHALED KHALED. It is produced by Tennessee based Tay Keith and it features Atlanta rapper Lil Baby and Chicago rapper Lil Durk.

While Khaled and Baby had collabed on two different occasions prior to this on You Stay and Weather the Storm, this is the first collab between Khaled and Durk. Lil Baby and Durk however, have numerous collaborations to their names and there is even a joint mixtape between them being teased to be released soon.

songs.title: Nas Album Done

description.plain:
“Nas Album Done” serves as a preview of sorts for Nas' own upcoming album (i.e. the title of this song).

Nas touches on issues facing minorities in America throughout the song, including Donald Trump’s bid for President and institutionalized inequalities.

Khaled wrote a letter thanking the Fugees for clearing this song’s “Fu-Gee-La” sample.

Dj Khaled premiered a trailer on his Instagram to promote the short film, while releasing it 3 days later on his Youtube Vevo channel. The short film features Louie Rankin, better known as Ox from the movie “Belly.” The short film was shot in Nassau (the capital city of the Bahamas) and directed by Eif Rivera and Dj Khaled himself.
